            "answer_text": " \u201cInverted commas\u201d are used to enclose direct speech or a quotation. In the US and Canada, double quotation marks are traditionally chosen. In Britain, single quotation marks set off quoted speech. But only the leading quotation marks are inverted commas (\u201c). The trailing quotation marks are raised (but not inverted) commas (\u201d). Single marks are traditionally preferred with double marks inside them as required then single again and so on. \u2018He asked me, \u201cWill you pick up a copy of \u2018The Thousand Splendid Suns\u2019 for me?\u201d\u2019 Which ones you use is up to you. ",
